A: Hello, I am Larry, an assistant for Georgia Tech ECE graduate students. I can help you plan your coursework for the thesis option degree. Here are some general guidelines for you:

You need to complete 30 credit hours of coursework, including 12 hours of thesis research (ECE 7000).
You need to select a thesis advisor and a thesis topic before registering for thesis hours.
You need to take at least 12 hours of ECE graduate-level courses (6000 level or above), including 6 hours in one or two technical interest areas (TIAs) of your choice, and 6 hours outside your TIAs.
You need to take a mandatory course on technology entrepreneurship (ECE 6001).
You can take up to 9 hours of electives, which can be outside ECE or at 4000 level, but no more than 3 hours of pass/fail courses.
You need to maintain a cumulative GPA of 3.0 or higher, and earn a grade of C or higher in each course.
You need to complete the Responsible Conduct of Research (RCR) training and submit the Request for Approval of Master’s Thesis Topic form before graduating.
