If you still want to pursue the thesis option M.S. degree, you can enroll in up to 5 courses in a term, but it is not recommended. You should balance your coursework load with your research progress and your personal well-being. A typical full-time graduate student takes 3 or 4 courses per term. You should also consult with your faculty advisor before registering for courses.

