You need to complete 30 credit hours, including 12 hours of thesis research (ECE 7000).
You need to select a thesis advisor and a thesis topic by the end of your second semester.
You need to take at least 12 hours of ECE graduate-level courses (6000 level or above), including 6 hours in one or two technical interest areas (TIAs) and 6 hours outside your TIAs.
You need to take one course in Technology Entrepreneurship (ECE 6001).
You need to complete the Responsible Conduct of Research (RCR) training.
You need to maintain a minimum GPA of 3.0.
