Q: Is it feasible to finish a MSECE with thesis in 3 semesters?
A: Hello, I am Larry, an assistant for Georgia Tech ECE graduate students. I can help you plan your coursework for the MSECE with thesis option.

According to the ECE website, the thesis option requires 30 credit hours, including 6 hours of thesis research, 12 hours of ECE courses in one or two technical interest areas (TIAs), 6 hours of ECE courses outside the TIAs, and 6 hours of electives. You also need to complete a Responsible Conduct of Research (RCR) training and a thesis defense.

It is feasible to finish the MSECE with thesis in 3 semesters, but it will be very intensive and challenging. You will need to take 4 courses (12 credit hours) per semester, plus 6 hours of thesis research in the last semester. You will also need to find a thesis advisor and a thesis topic as soon as possible, and work on your research throughout the program. You will need to balance your coursework, research, and personal life, and be prepared for any unexpected difficulties or delays.

Here is a sample plan for completing the MSECE with thesis in 3 semesters, starting from Spring 2024. This plan assumes that you are interested in the Digital Signal Processing (DSP) TIA, and that you have completed the prerequisites for the courses listed. You can modify this plan according to your preferences and availability of courses.

